{{nihongo|'''''Cantarella'''''|カンタレラ|Kantarera|lead=yes}} is a [[manga]] series by [[You Higuri]], serialized in the Japanese monthly comic magazine ''Princess Gold Magazine'' and published in ''[[tankōbon]]'' format by [[Akita Shoten]]. The first volume was published March 2001 and there have been 12 volumes published in Japan as of July 2010. The series went on a four-year two-month hiatus in ''Princess Gold Magazine'', resuming in the September 2009 issue.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-08-17/you-higuri-resumes-cantarella-manga-after-4-year-break|title=You Higuri Resumes Cantarella Manga After 4-Year Break|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2009-08-17|accessdate=2010-01-14}}</ref> ''Cantarella'' has also been translated into Traditional Chinese by [[Ever Glory Publishing]] in Taiwan (also sale to Hong Kong), French by [[Asuka (publisher)|Asuka]] (first volume May 2005), German by [[Carlsen Comics]], English by [[Go! Comi]] (first volume October 2005), Russian by Palma Press (Палма Пресс) (first volume July 2010) and Italian by Free Books.
==Plot== Cantarella is the story of [[Cesare Borgia]], an [[Italy|Italian]] [[Aristocracy (class)|aristocrat]] during the [[Renaissance]]. In the [[manga]], [[Cesare Borgia|Cesare]]'s father [[Rodrigo Borgia]], a [[cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]], sells his infant son's soul to the [[Devil]] as part of a deal that will one day make him [[Pope]] (Rodrigo will become Pope with the name of [[Pope Alexander VI|Alexander VI]]). Cesare is consequently shunned by his father, who is unable to see him as anything but an agent of darkness and reminder of his [[sin]]. Increasingly alienated, Cesare eventually comes to rely on the dark powers within himself. He becomes obsessed with the idea of conquest, and is aided in his political machinations by the [[assassination|assassin]] Don Michelotto.
