'''''Failure Magazine''''' is an online [[magazine]] which features stories about [[failure]]. The magazine was established in 2000 by Jason Zasky<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/30/AR2008103004095.html|title=When All Else Fails, He Writes About It |first=Dan |last=Zak|work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=November 2, 2008  |publisher=[[Washington Post Company|WPC]] |location=[[Washington, DC|Washington DC]] |issn=0190-8286|accessdate=22 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://money.cnn.com/magazines/fortune/fortune_archive/2000/09/04/286788/index.htm |title=A Bet That Failure Pays Off Big |first=Alynda |last=Wheat|work=CNN|date=4 September 2000 |accessdate=22 August 2013}}</ref> and his cousin.<ref name=han>{{cite book|author1=H. Albert Napier|author2=Ollie Rivers|author3=Stuart Wagner|title=Creating a Winning E-Business|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IZQFAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA39|accessdate=21 November 2015|date=22 December 2005|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=1-111-79609-2|page=39}}</ref> It is headquartered in [[New York City]].<ref name=han/> The magazine turned its first profit in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecollegetimes.com/student-life/this-failure-generates-success-1.2498833#.UhZ3KW37bm0 |title=This 'Failure' Generates Success - Student Life - College Times - Serving Arizona State University and Valley colleges |first=Arthur |last=Martori |work=Ecollege Times |date=March 16, 2006 |accessdate=22 August 2013 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The magazine features a column called, "This day in failure".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://odewire.com/61985/in-praise-of-failure.html |title=In praise of failure &#124; OdeWire |first=Marisa |last=Taylor |work=odewire.com |date=8 September 2008|accessdate=22 August 2013}}</ref>

